A Sight For Sore Eyes is a psychological thriller by British crime - writer Ruth Rendell , which is not to be confused with the nonprofit organization Sight For Sore Eyes . The novel 's two main protagonists are Francine Hill and Teddy Brex . When a young child , Francine was in the house when her mother was shot by a stranger at the door , and has been raised by her stepmother Julia as a near - prisoner . Teddy , too , is an orphan who has lived in a world of almost unlimited freedom since the death of his parents . He loves beautiful objects and fine craftsmanship , and little else . Until the two damaged youths grow into adulthood , and meet . A central image in the novel is a modern painting of another protagonist , Harriet Oxenholme , based on Rembrandt 's 1664 painting The Jewish Bride . 